IPL 2023 was the 16th edition of the Indian Premier League, a popular Twenty20 cricket tournament held in India. It featured eight teams representing different cities across the country. Matches were played at various stadiums across India from March/April to May. 
The teams that participated in IPL 2023 were Chennai Super Kings, Delhi Capitals, Kings XI Punjab, Kolkata Knight Riders, Mumbai Indians, Rajasthan Royals, Royal Challengers Bangalore, and Sunrisers Hyderabad. 
The tournament followed a round-robin format, where each team played against every other team twice, once at home and once away. The top four teams advanced to the playoffs. 
The playoffs consisted of Eliminator, Qualifier 1, Eliminator 2, and the Final. The final match, which determined the IPL 2023 champion, was played at a prestigious stadium selected by the BCCI. 
IPL 2023 showcased exceptional performances from established international players and emerging talents, with batsmen displaying power-hitting skills and bowlers showcasing variations and strategies. 
The tournament witnessed high fan engagement, with enthusiastic crowds filling the stadiums and creating a vibrant atmosphere. Fans also participated through social media, contests, merchandise, and promotional activities. 
IPL 2023 was broadcasted live on television and streamed online, reaching millions of viewers worldwide. 
Prior to the tournament, teams participated in an IPL auction to acquire new players and strengthen their squads. The auction saw intense bidding wars and strategic team-building exercises. 
Overall, IPL 2023 provided an exciting and thrilling cricketing experience, featuring top-notch skills, intense rivalries, and memorable moments, captivating fans across the globe.
